EXT. FEDERAL COMPLIANCE FIELD OFFICE - NIGHT

The gravel lot behind the storefront, empty, chain-link, the HARMONY IS A VERB poster lit faint through the glass.

A pickup idles at the lot's edge, lights off. GUNNY, STITCH, and DUTCH climb out, unhurried, like men who've done harder things together before.

STITCH:
(low)
Never thought I'd see you out past nine, Dutch.

DUTCH:
Never thought a supply captain's favor would get held against me fifty years later either. Man adjusts.

Gunny sets a mortar tube in a coffee can of sand. Stitch touches a punk stick to a road flare until it catches.

GUNNY:
Fire in the hole, gentlemen.

The first shell goes up with a crack that lights the whole lot red, then green, then a shower of gold that hangs a long time over the flat highway dark.

Three old men stand in the falling light, faces turned up, not moving.

A second shell. A third.

On the fourth, headlights swing into the lot. The car eases to a stop. WADE gets out, hand nowhere near his holster, looks at the sky a second before he looks at them.

WADE:
(finally)
Evening, gentlemen. Y'all want to tell me whose idea this was, or should I guess?

GUNNY:
Mine.

DUTCH:
His, but I brought the truck.

STITCH:
I just held the lighter. Following orders.

WADE:
(getting out his citation book, slow)
Turn around for me. All three of you.

INT. COUNTY COURTHOUSE, COURTROOM - DAY

A small county courtroom, half empty. Gunny, Dutch, and Stitch at the defense table, one good jacket each. In the gallery, alone in a middle row: Cricket, hat in his lap. A YOUNG PROSECUTOR shuffles papers. JUDGE ORVAL BENNING, 70s, black robe, reading glasses low on his nose.

CLERK:
(reading)
Unlawful discharge of consumer fireworks, three counts. Trespass on federal leasehold, three counts.

JUDGE BENNING:
(not looking up)
How do the defendants plead?

GUNNY:
Guilty, Your Honor. All three counts, all three of us.

JUDGE BENNING:
(to the prosecutor)
Anybody hurt?

PROSECUTOR:
No, Your Honor.

JUDGE BENNING:
Property damage?

PROSECUTOR:
A scorched patch of gravel, Your Honor.

JUDGE BENNING:
(a long look at them over his glasses)
I was nine years old in my daddy's living room the night men from this state walked on the Moon. Watched it on a television the size of a bread box.
(beat)
Time served. Four hundred dollars each, plus the cost of the gravel. I've got real criminals on this morning's docket, gentlemen. Get on home.

He bangs the gavel before the prosecutor can get a word in.

EXT. COUNTY COURTHOUSE - DAY

The three of them come down the steps into the sun. Cricket is waiting at the bottom, leaning on his truck, arms crossed.

Gunny stops on the step above him. A beat.

GUNNY:
Come to gloat?

CRICKET:
Came to drive you home. Your truck's still at the lot. Wade's got it towed.

Stitch and Dutch come down past them, already arguing about whose fine is bigger.

Gunny looks at Cricket a moment longer.

GUNNY:
You could've come.

CRICKET:
I know it.

Neither says anything else. Gunny claps him once on the shoulder, hard, and gets in the truck.

CUT TO:
